<h2>The weather in December 2019</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
In December, the whole of Europe experienced exceptionally above average temperatures (Figure 6). Anomalies for minimum, average and maximum temperatures are largely above 2&deg;C (Figure 5) and increase towards the East with maximum values of 5&deg;C and more observed over Russia and Finland.
