<h3>Radiation and Cloudiness</h3>
<br><br>
In December it was less cloudy than normal over most parts of Europe, corresponding to a positive anomaly in incoming radiation (figure 14). Only Scandinavia and the northwestern part of Russia experienced more cloudy than normal conditions and thus a deficit in radiation.
